# Quadratic Regression for Rear Stagger Optimization â€“ Pavement Midget Racing

This project builds predictive single-variable quadratic models to determine the optimal rear-stagger setting (RS) for qualifying at Lucas Oil Indianapolis Raceway Park.

Rear stagger is defined as:
**RS = (CRR âˆ’ CLR)**  
The goal is to model how RS affects lap time and identify the stagger that produces the fastest lap.

(Source: *Project 2.2 PDF*, MSPE 29800, Purdue University) :contentReference[oaicite:2]{index=2}

